<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>off one’s game • off the game</xh5><p> <i>off one’s game</i>—(of a sportsman) playing badly: I backed Tommy when most folk thought he was <u>off his game</u>!</p><p> <i>off the game</i>—(of a sportsman) not playing: When I am <u>off the game</u> or off work, the first few days I would like to relax at home with my family.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression is not equivalent in meaning to the phrase <b>out of the game</b>—(of a sportsman) remaining out of play during a game: I was <u>out of the game</u> and useless. That’s my first memory as a player.</p><p> <i>See also: on one’s game / on the game.</i></p></entry>
